The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Aug. 12: Indias forex reserves 

 increased by $1.77 billion to $165.795 billion in the week 

 ended August 4 compared with $164.023 billion in the week 

 ended July 28. The reserves had increased by $675 million 

 during the preceding week ended July 28, compared with a 

 week-ago period. Foreign currency assets increased by $1.394 

 billion to $158.465 billion during the reporting week, according 

 to figures released by the reserve bank of India today. 

 Foreign currency assets in dollars include the effect of 

 re-evaluation of non-US currencies such as the euro, sterling 

 and yen held in reserves. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 12: LML has allotted 12.58 

 lakh equity shares to foreign institutional investor Credit 

 Suisse (Singapore) upon conversion of foreign currency convertible 

 bonds. 

 Calcutta, Aug. 12: Tata Steel, which 

 has entered into organised retailing by setting up Steeljunction 

 in the city, is working on a business plan to develop this 

 line of activity in other cities as well.




